    "department": "Finance",
    "description": "ABOUT PAVE BANK:\n\nWelcome to Pave Bank, where we’re not just reimagining banking—we’re transforming it! Inspired by global fintech pioneers and powered by data-driven ingenuity, we are building smarter, faster, and more accessible banking solutions that prioritize innovation and customer experience. Based in Tbilisi, Georgia, we combine the agility of a startup with the reliability of a well-regulated institution, empowering individuals and businesses to shape their financial futures.\n\nOur culture thrives on collaboration, innovation, and a passion for cutting-edge technology. Join us on our mission to redefine what banking can be—and make a real impact in a dynamic, fast-paced environment. Together, we’ll pave the way to a brighter financial world.\n\n\nYOUR MISSION HERE AT PAVE BANK:\n\nAs an Accountant at Pave Bank, you’re more than a number-cruncher; you’ll be at the heart of our financial ecosystem, ensuring accuracy, compliance and strategic insight in everything we do. With a high degree of agility and a proactive mindset, this role offers the great opportunity to navigate the complexities of fintech and to shape the financial strategies of a growing fintech startup in one of the world’s most regulated and innovative industries.\n\n\nWHAT YOU’LL DO:\n\n - Be the Financial Pillar: Create accurate and timely financial reports (monthly, quarterly, annually, or as and when required) and ensure flawless reconciliation. Your work will shape the backbone of our financial health.\n\n - Strategic Thinker: Analyze complex financial data, identify trends, and turn numbers into actionable strategies that drive business decisions.\n\n - Regulatory Champion: Prepare statutory filings/ad hoc reports and submit to National Bank of Georgia and other regulators as required, ensuring we meet every requirement with precision and timeliness.\n\n - Audit Ace: Lead annual and interim audits, championing transparency and compliance.\n\n - Collaborative Innovator: Be a Business Partner across teams such as Tech, Product, Treasury and beyond to build a robust financial framework that supports our growth.\n\n - Policy Guardian: Keep us aligned with company policies and government regulations, ensuring every transaction is as clean as it is compliant.\n\n\nTO BE SUCCESSFUL:\n\n - A degree in Finance, Accounting or related professional qualification, showcasing your expertise (CA, ACCA, etc).\n\n - Strong knowledge in International Financial Reporting Standards especially IFRS 9 and financial instruments\n\n - At least 3-4 years of experience in Big 4 Accounting Firms - bonus points for fintech or financial services exposure!\n\n - Advanced Excel skills (including macros and Power Query) and the ability to handle large data sets like a pro.\n\n - The ability to thrive in a fast-paced, deadline-driven environment without breaking a sweat.\n\n - A sharp eye for detail, paired with an innovative and solution-driven mindset.\n\n - A love for teamwork but the confidence to work independently with tight deadlines and minimum supervision when needed.\n\n\nWHY US?\n\n - Cutting-Edge Innovation: Work at the forefront of fintech, where every day brings fresh challenges and opportunities.\n\n - Dynamic Team: Collaborate with passionate, driven professionals who love what they do.\n\n - Startup Energy, Solid Foundation: Enjoy the agility of a startup with the stability of a regulated financial institution.\n\n - Your Voice Matters: At Pave Bank, your ideas and contributions directly impact our growth and success.",
    "employment_type": "FullTime",
